bs: Add forgotten codeql.yml to EXTRA_DIST

Add the forgotten file .github/workflows/codeql.yml to
EXTRA_DIST should fix "make distcheck".

Remove unused log_data() function

Remove unused log_data() function. If we ever need it, we can just
re-add it later.
bs: _FORTIFY_SOURCE appears to also require -O, so combine them

i6b: Add NULL check to silence gcc warning

gcc 13 finds that console_device is checked for NULL after
dereferencing it.

This should not be a problem as

    int main(int argc, char *argv[]) should never be called

with a NULL pointer in the argv[] array, but we want to silence
all compiler warnings, and this does not hurt us.
QI build permissions: read should be sufficient
bs: Tell clang to accept the GNU line markers it produces itself
bs: Check for -Wa,-adhlns= before using it

clang: Use proper -Wmost instead of -Weverything

The -Weverything flag is only intended to use when testing clang itself,
so use the -Wmost flag for our production code.

CREDITS.md: Add heading to help pandoc find a title

Note that we are using the "# Title" form of writing a Markdown
heading even though it is less nice to read as text than the
form with a ====== underlining the title.

The reason is to work around git confusing the ======= together
with the Markdown block quotes below ("> ") with leftover conflict
markers and refusing to commit.
ci: Add CodeQL workflow for the C code
i6b: Clarify message
rename safe_error_exit() to safe_errno_exit()

SIGHUP is another way to die

As a SIGHUP is another way for a process to be killed,
silence the speaker properly on SIGHUP before aborting
the program like we already do on SIGINT and SIGTERM.

improve code readability through better alignment

Proper alignment makes similar things look similar, while
making the differences stand out more.
doc: sigaction(2), -std=gnu99, and misc small fixes
rename signal handler
bs: add FROM to rule description output
bs: quieten doxygen if V=

bs: Define CFLAGS and common_CFLAGS as = var, not :=

As the flags checks happen only once anyway, we do not need
to define CFLAGS and common_CFLAGS as a := style variable
and a standard = style variable works as well.

bs: Print Rule Descriptions w/ and w/o Silent Rules

Print a rule description for every make rule every time, but
format them adequately for running with silent rules and for
running without silent rules.
bs: Describe GNU make usage and link to GNU make papers

bs: Use Deferred Simple Variable Expansion

Use Deferred Simple Variable Expansion for PACKAGE_TARBASE.

This is not a big gain, but a step in the right direction.

bs: Group install-nobuild definitions

As it does not matter where "FOO = " type variables
are defined, we can define the "inhibit-build-command"
together with the "install-nobuild" target, which
groups logically connected things together.

bs: No need to explicitly list the *dir variables

We can just filter the list of variables $(.VARIABLES)
for all variables whose name ends in dir.

bs: use GNU make -C param in "distcheck" rule

We are relying on GNU make, so we can rely on its -C parameter.
